[SN]TITLE[SN]
Bristol toddler donates bone marrow to try and save brother

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A Bristol toddler has donated bone marrow to try and save the life of his older brother who has cancer.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Media playback is unsupported on your device
25 April 2014 Last updated at 01:05 BST
Three-year-old Chase Rowe had the operation after his brother Kenzie was told his leukaemia had returned.
Seven-year-old Kenzie was given the all clear last year, but tests have revealed that the cancer has returned.
His mother has been warned that if the transplant fails the NHS may not offer any further treatment.
Fiona Lamdin met the family.
